{"word":"ἔλδομαι","slug":"ἔλδομαι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἔλδομαι</b></el> <p/><i>to wish, long</i> to do a thing, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b>Hom</b>: —<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a> <i>to long for</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>: <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to desire</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>:—as <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>νῦν τοι ἐελδέσθω πόλεμος</el> <i>be</i> war now <i>welcome</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>only in <a href='S:present tense'>pres.</a> and <a href='S:imperfect tense'>imperf.</a>\n"}]}